<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Very small moths, among the smallest in body size within 
<taxonomicName family="Mimallonidae" lsidName="" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" rank="family">Mimallonidae</taxonomicName>
, with forewing length ranging from 9-11 mm. Coloration also diagnostic: wing ground color yellow with purplish-pink antemedial regions. Ventrum of both fore- and hindwings with apparent antemedial as well as postmedial lines.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="apomorphy">
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Apomorphy.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="11">(1) Uncus and a subuncal sclerotization fused, heavily sclerotized apically forming a conical structure with tegumen (Fig. 2a).</paragraph>
